## TL;DR: Antique Cushion Cut Diamond Ring — What You Need to Know First

An antique cushion cut diamond ring is either a genuine estate piece centered on an old mine cut diamond (pre-1920s, chunky crown, large culet, asymmetric facets) or a new ring built on a vintage-style setting with a modern cushion diamond — and these are two fundamentally different purchases with different price structures and availability. Vintage-style cushion ring builds at Blue Nile start at [$1,190 for the Art Deco Fleur-De-Lis Pavé setting](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/art-deco-inspired-fleur-de-lis-pave-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315298?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (102 reviews); the best complete vintage-inspired build is a [GIA 1ct G-VS1 cushion at $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) plus the [Infinity Vintage-Style 14K White Gold at $1,455](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/infinity-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315144?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (202 reviews) for **$3,346 total**. **→ Best first pick: [IGI 1.5ct E-VVS2 Lab Cushion at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [Art Deco Fleur-De-Lis Pavé at $1,190](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/art-deco-inspired-fleur-de-lis-pave-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315298?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = $2,612 total — a vintage-aesthetic cushion ring at entry price with superior stone quality over any comparable genuine antique at that budget.**

