## Antique Cushion Cut Halo Ring

An antique cushion cut halo ring places a row of accent diamonds around the cushion center in a configuration that echoes the cluster rings of Victorian and Edwardian fine jewelry — where a central cushion old mine cut was surrounded by a halo of smaller old mine cuts in a closed, pavé-style mount. The modern version replaces the old mine accent diamonds with round brilliants and the handmade mount with a precision-machined halo head, but the visual effect — a cushion diamond amplified by a surrounding ring of diamonds — is historically accurate to the period.

The halo amplifies an antique cushion ring's visual impact in exactly the same way it amplifies modern cushion rings: by extending the diamond footprint 20–30% beyond the center stone's actual edge, creating a combined face-up area significantly larger than the center stone alone. At vintage-era L/W ratios (1.00–1.10 for old mine cushions, which tend toward near-square), a halo creates a pronounced rounded-square visual that reads as distinctly Victorian. At modern elongated ratios (1.15–1.25), the same halo creates a more rectangular outline.

**The [Interlaced Pavé Halo Vintage-Style Engagement Ring in 14K White Gold at $1,750](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/interlaced-pave-halo-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-316222?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (29 reviews) is the most historically coherent halo option in the Blue Nile vintage collection — the interlaced band pattern replicates the braided or woven metalwork conventions of Edwardian jewelry more accurately than flat-pavé halo settings that read as modern.** Pair it with a near-square cushion (1.00–1.08 L/W) to maximize the Victorian cluster aesthetic; pair it with a 1.15–1.20 cushion for a more contemporary silhouette with period detail. Full halo analysis in our [Halo Cushion Cut Diamond Ring guide](/halo-cushion-cut-diamond-ring).

## Antique Cushion Solitaire Ring

An antique cushion solitaire ring — a single old mine or vintage-aesthetic cushion in a plain or lightly detailed setting without a halo — is the format that most directly showcases the cushion's antique cut characteristics. Without accent diamonds competing for attention, The Old Mine Window's large-flash sparkle pattern, the high-crown profile, and the organic silhouette are fully visible and uninterrupted. This is the format chosen by buyers who specifically want the old mine cut's optical character, not the antique period's metalwork.

In new vintage-inspired rings, the antique solitaire aesthetic is best served by a setting with milgrain prong edges rather than plain prongs — the milgrain beading at the prong base is the detail that signals period metalwork from across the room. The [Embossed Vintage-Style Engagement Ring in 14K White Gold at $2,135](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/embossed-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-305209?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (81 reviews) and the [Milgrain Navette Vintage-Style in 14K White Gold at $1,950](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/milgrain-navette-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315113?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (38 reviews) both achieve this — a solitaire head with enough setting detail to read as antique while keeping the center stone as the clear visual dominant.

**Yellow gold is the authentically correct metal for a Victorian-era antique cushion solitaire — platinum was not used in engagement rings until Edwardian period, and yellow gold with a cushion modified brilliant creates the warmest, most historically grounded antique solitaire aesthetic available in a new ring.** The [Milgrain and Pavé V-Shank at $1,790](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/milgrain-and-pave-v-shank-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-8-ct-wt-item-203569?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (36 reviews) in yellow gold with a G-H color cushion is the most historically accurate complete antique solitaire aesthetic available from a major retailer. See full solitaire analysis in our [Cushion Cut Diamond Solitaire Ring guide](/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-ring).

